direction.raw_text: I trusted him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You trusted him? When? When he promised you half his share?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (offended) No! His whole share. Plus, he told me he'd done it before. Arthur turns to Cobb.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Oh, yeah? With Mal? That worked out great, didn't it, Cobb? Cobb grabs Arthur.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You don't know anything about that. This was the only way to do this job, Arthur. I did what I had to do to get back to my children.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So you led us into a war zone with no way out.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We have a way out. The kick. We just have to push on, do the job as fast as possible and get out using the kick.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Forget it. We go any deeper, we just raise the stakes. I'm sitting it out on this level.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You'll never make it, Eames. Fischer's security is surrounding this place as we speak. The ten hours of the flight is a week at this level-you'll never make it without getting killed. Downwards is the only way forwards. We have to carry on. Saito groans. Cobb looks at him-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And we have to do it fast. Eames and Arthur weigh this.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Eames, go get ready. Arthur, let's get in there and soften him up. INT. BATHROOM, WAREHOUSE - LATER Cobb and Arthur, wearing BALACLAVAS, PULL the sack from Fischer's head. He is chained to the radiator.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm insured against kidnapping up to ten million-this'll be simple-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, it won't. Fischer looks at Cobb, unnerved.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: In. your lather's office, below the bookshelves, is his personal safe. We need the combination.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I never noticed a safe-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Doesn't mean you don't know the combination.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Well, I don't.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We have it on good authority that you do.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Whose? INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS Yusuf looks through Fischer's wallet. Eames is opening a HINGED, THREE-WING MIRROR.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Five hundred dollars, this cost?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What's inside?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Cash, cards, ID... and this- Yusuf holds up a SNAPSHOT: the photo from Maurice Fischer's office- YOUNG ROBERT holds his HOMEMADE PINWHEEL, his FATHER blows on it. Eames takes it from Yusuf. STUDIES it. Cobb enters. Eames hands him the snapshot.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Useful? Cobb studies the snapshot. Eames examines himself in the hinged mirror from multiple angles: ONE BY ONE the myriad Eames reflections BECOME BROWNINGS. Cobb pockets the photo.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're on. You've got an hour.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: An hour? I was supposed to have all night to crack him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And Saito was supposed to keep his guts on the inside. You've got an hour-get something we can use. Eames turns from the mirror AS BROWNING. He glances at his watch, then SCREAMS, as if begging for mercy- INT. BATHROOM, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS Browning's CRY reverberates- Fischer looks up, concerned-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What's that?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Good authority. Another cry rings out. Fischer recognizes the voice.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Uncle Peter?! Make them stop-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The combination.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I don't know it!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Why would Browning tell us you did?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Let me talk to him-I'll find out.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . INT. BATHROOM, WAREHOUSE - MOMENTS LATER Cobb pushes Browning (Eames), bloody and bruised, into the room and forces him down next to Fischer. Cobb handcuffs Browning's wrist to a metal bracket on the side of the sink.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You've got an hour. Get talking. Cobb leaves.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They've had me for two days. They've got someone with access to your father's office and they're trying to open his safe-they thought I'd know the combination, but I don't-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Neither do I, Uncle Peter.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (confused) Maurice told me that after he passed only you would be able to open it.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He never gave me the combination. Browning thinks for a minute. Realizes something.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He did, he just didn't tell you that it was a combination.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What, then?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Something only you would know. Some meaningful combination of numbers from your experiences with Maurice-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We didn't have a lot of meaningful experiences together.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Perhaps after your mother died...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: After my mother died, I went to him in my grief. (MORE)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You know what he told me? "There's really nothing to be said, Robert."
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He always had a hard time with emotional-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I was eleven, Uncle Peter. Browning (Eames) takes this in.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He loved you, Robert. In his way.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: "In his way?" At the end he called me to his deathbed. He could barely speak, but he took the trouble to say one last thing to me. He pulled me close... I could make out only one word. "Disappointed." Browning can say nothing. INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS Cobb pulls off his balaclava. Looks down at Saito, who is breathing fast, shallow.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: How's he doing?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He's in a lot of pain. Cobb takes Saito's hand. Looks him in the eye.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: When we get you down to the next level, the pain will be less intense. Saito nods, breathing hard.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (low) And if he dies?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: His conscious mind will drop out of the dream. He'll be trapped in Limbo for a lifetime...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What will that do to him?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . Cobb looks at her. Grave.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: When he wakes... his mind could be completely gone.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: When... when we wake I will still honor our arrangement... Cobb looks down at Saito sadly.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Saito-san, when you wake you might not even remember that we had an arrangement. You'll have forgotten this world. Limbo will be your reality. Lost there so long, you'll have become an old man...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Filled with regret?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Waiting to die alone. Yes.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Then I'll take the chance and come back. And we'll be young men together again. Saito smiles weakly. Cobb nods at him, turns to Ariadne.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: When were you trapped in Limbo? Cobb says nothing. Ariadne pulls him away from Saito.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Cobb, you might have convinced the rest of this team to carry on with the job. But they don't know the truth.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What truth?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The truth that at any minute you might bring a freight train through the wall. The truth that Mal is bursting up through your subconscious. (MORE)
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The truth that as we go deeper into Fischer, we're also going deeper into you-and I'm not sure we're going to like what we find there. Cobb stares back at Ariadne. Saying nothing.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: This is not just about Fischer, it's about you. Tell me what happened to you and Mal. Trapped in Limbo. Cobb looks at her. Thinking it through.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We were on a job. Exploring dreams within dreams. But we didn't understand how your mind can turn hours into years. How you can get trapped. Trapped so deep that when you wash up on the shore of your subconscious... INSERT CUT: MAL LIES ON THE SAND, STARING UP AT A CLOUDLESS SKY, WAVES WASHING OVER HER...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You can lose track of what's real.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: How long were you stuck? Cobb pauses before he answers. Looks at Ariadne.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Fifty years. Ariadne stares at him, incredulous.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: How did you stand it? INSERT CUT: COBB AND MAL BUILD A SANDCASTLE ON THE BEACH...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We built. We created a whole world for ourselves... INSERT CUT: COBB AND MAL WALK THROUGH A DESERTED CITY.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's not so bad at first, being gods. The problem is knowing that it's not real. It became impossible for me to live like that.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: But not for her?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She accepted it. At some point... INSERT CUT: INT. MAL'S CHILDHOOD HOME - DAY Mal opens a DOLL'S HOUSE. Inside is a SAFE. She opens it- it is empty. She pulls out her SPINNING TOP.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: ...she'd decided to forget that our world wasn't real. Mal places the top inside the safe. LOCKS IT AWAY... INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS ARIADNE And when you finally woke up?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: To wake from that. From decades lived. To be old souls thrown back into youth. It was hard. At first Mal seemed okay. But I started to realize something was wrong. Finally she admitted it. This idea she was possessed by. This simple little idea that changed everything...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What was it?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: That our world was not real. No matter what I did, no matter what I said, she was convinced that we were still in a dream. That we needed to wake up again... INT. COBB AND MAL'S KITCHEN - DAY (FLASHBACK) Cobb is trying to calm Mal, who is hysterical.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: That to get home we'd have to kill ourselves. INT. WORKSHOP - DAY Ariadne looks at Cobb, appalled.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What about your children? Cobb has to look away.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She... she believed they weren't real. That our real children were waiting. Somewhere above... INT. COBB AND MAL'S KITCHEN - DAY (FLASHBACK) Mal shakes her head at Cobb as he USHERS the children out of the room, FACES UNSEEN- COBB Calm down, Mal-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They're projections, Dom. Your dreams. I'm their mother-don't you think I can tell the difference? Cobb closes the door- turns to her, eyes full of bitter tears.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: If it's my dream then why can't I control it? Why can't I stop this?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (it's obvious) You don't know you're dreaming.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You keep telling me I am-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And you don't believe me!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She was certain. But she loved me too much to go without me. So she made a plan... INT. ELEGANT HOTEL CORRIDOR - NIGHT (FLASHBACK) Cobb walks along, checking door numbers against a key.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: For our anniversary... INT. ELEGANT HOTEL SUITE - CONTINUOUS (FLASHBACK) Cobb enters the lavish suite. He notices the DISHEVELED BEDCLOTHES.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . He steps forwards- SMASH- he has tipped over a champagne glass with his foot... dinner for two is SPREAD ACROSS THE FLOOR. He looks at the DEBRIS, confused... next to the broken glass is a SPINNING TOP. He picks it up, studying it, thinking. He feels a draught, looks to the window. The CURTAIN BILLOWS. EXT. EXTERIOR ATRIUM - CONTINUOUS (FLASHBACK) Cobb looks out the window: Mal sits on the ledge of the opposite window. HAIR BLOWING. Feet dangling over the dizzyingly high atrium. She smiles.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Join me.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Mal, come back inside.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No. I'm going to jump. And you're coming with me.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No, I'm not. This is real-if you jump, you're not going to wake up, you're going to die. Let's go back inside and talk about this, please.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We've talked enough. She KICKS off a shoe and watches it DROP.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Come out onto the ledge or I'll jump right now. She means it. Cobb swings his legs out, sitting on the ledge opposite is wife. He looks down at the drop.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm asking you to take a leap of faith.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I can't do that, Mal. I can't leave our children.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: If I go without you, they'll take them away, anyway.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What do you mean?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I filed a letter with our attorney. Explaining how I'm fearful for my safety, how you've threatened to kill me... Cobb looks back at the wrecked hotel suite, PANICKING...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I love you, Dom. I've freed you from the guilt of choosing to leave them. We're going home to our real children.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Out children are here, Mal. Mal CLOSES HER EYES. Cobb looks for some way to reach her...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're waiting for a train...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: ! MAL, NO, I CAN'T!
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: A train that will take you far away...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You know where you hope this train will take you, you can't know for sure...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: But it doesn't matter...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Because you'll be together... Mal SLIPS FORWARD INTO SPACE. Cobb SCREAMS after her. Then tries to bury his face in the wall... INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - DAY Cobb stares as he remembers.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: He letter to the authorities refuted all the claims about her sanity that she knew I'd make... INT. COBB AND MAL'S KITCHEN - DAY (FLASHBACK) Cobb stands with the Thin Man, who has a piece of paper.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She'd had herself declared sane by three different psychiatrists. Cobb hears a SHOUT- turns to the garden. James CROUCHES, Philippa joins him, examining the ground, FACES UNSEEN...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It was impossible for me to explain the nature of her madness... The Thin Man thrusts the paper into Cobb's hand.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Right now. Or never, Cobb. Cobb turns back to the window- about to call out- James and Philippa RUN OFF. Cobb turns from the window. Looks at the paper in his hand. It is an AIRPLANE TICKET.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So I ran. And I've been running ever since, trying to buy my way back to my family... INT. OFFICE, WAREHOUSE - DAY Cobb looks across at Ariadne.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Psychiatrists judged her sane?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: She was sane. She was just lost in the labyrinth.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Then why should you blame yourself?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Because we were a family. And we had a life I would do anything to get back to now. But that reality wasn't enough for me then.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It might have been your idea to push the limits, Cobb. But you're not responsible for the idea that destroyed her. The idea that her world wasn't real... that was her own idea from her own mind. Cobb says nothing.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Your guilt defines her. Powers her. If we're going to succeed in this, you're going to have to forgive yourself, and you're going to have to confront her. But you don't have to do it alone.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You don't have to do this for me-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm doing it for the others. They don't know the risk they've taken coming in here with you. Cobb looks at the rooftop opposite, sees a SNIPER take up a position. Cobb shakes his head, frustrated.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We can't stay here. Arthur?! INT. BATHROOM, WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS Browning puts his hand on Fischer's shoulder.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: These people are going to kill us if we don't give them the combination.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: They won't, they'll try to ransom us-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I heard them-they're going to lock us in and run the can into the river.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What is in the safe?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Something for you. Maurice always said it was his most previous gift... a will.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Maurice's will is with Port and Dunn.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's an alternate. It supersedes the other only if you want it to.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What does it say?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It splits all the component businesses of Fischer Morrow into individual companies, transferring ownership to the boards of those companies...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Leaving me nothing?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: A basic living. Nothing more. The entire empire would cease to exist.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Destroy my own inheritance? Why would he suggest such a thing?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I don't know, Robert. Cobb OPENS the door. Arthur is behind him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Come to your senses?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Let us go. I don't know the combination. Not consciously. Cobb considers this. Opens his phone. Pulls out his gun.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Let's try instinctively. I have someone standing in your father's office ready to tap in a combination. He holds the phone to Fischer's mouth.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: First six numbers that come into your head. Right now.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I have no idea- Cobb SWINGS the gun onto Browning-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Five, two, eight... four, nine, one. Cobb lowers his weapon. Listens to the phone. Shakes his head. Shuts the phone.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You'll have to do better. Bag `em. Arthur puts SACKS over their heads. INT. WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS Cobb and Arthur drag Fischer and Browning to the van-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We're worth much more to you alive... Arthur places Fischer on the back seat- uses a DROPPER to drop LIQUID onto Fischer's mask- his head SLUMPS FORWARDS. "Browning" yanks the sack from his head- it is now EAMES.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (excited) His relationship with his father's much worse that we thought.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: That helps us? Arthur pulls a SNIPER RIFLE from a case by the van.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: The stronger the issues, the more powerful the catharsis. Cobb motions for Yusuf to follow his upstairs.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: But how do you reconcile them if they're that estranged?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm working on that. Arthur lines up a shot through the window-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Well, work fast-Fischer's projections are closing in quick, we need to break out of here before we're totally boxed in... Arthur SHOOTS two snipers. Cobb and Yusuf gently load Saito into the van. He groans. Ariadne straps him in, checks his bandages. Arthur can't get the last sniper- he's too hidden behind a wall-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Shouldn't be afraid to dream a little bigger, Arthur- Eames lines up a shot with a grenade launcher. Fires- the sniper EXPLODES into the air- Arthur looks at Eames.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Shall we? They climb into the van- INT./EXT. VAN ON RAINY STREETS - CONTINUOUS The van pulls out into the rain-drenched streets. Arthur opens the mechanism case and hands out tubes-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Shifting Fischer's antipathy from his father onto Browning should work.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We need the imagery, the words...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So you destroy his one positive relationship?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No. We repair his relationship with his father and expose his godfather's true nature.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Hell, we should be charging Fischer as much as Saito.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: What about his security? It's going to get worse as we go deeper.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: We bring in Mr. Charles.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Who's Mr. Charles?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: A bad idea.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Arthur, the second we approach Fischer in that hotel, they're gonna mow us down-we run with Mr. Charles like on the Stein job.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: So you've done it before?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sure. But it didn't work. The subject realized he was dreaming and his subconscious tore us to pieces. Eames takes this in.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You learned a lot, though. Right?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to Eames) I'll need a decoy.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No problem. How about a pretty young lady I've used before?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Fine- Cobb looks back: a second S.U.V. pulls out, tailing them.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (to Yusuf) I know you've got to stay ahead of them, but drive with kid gloves, okay? The world down there is going to be very unstable-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And don't make the jump too soon- that kick is our only way back, we have to be ready to catch it-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'll use the music to let you know when it's coming, but the rest is up to you. Arthur puts the mechanism onto the front seat.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Everyone ready? Nods all round.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Sweet dreams- Yusuf hits a button and we-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Am I boring you? Fischer looks up. A beautiful BLONDE is next to him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I was telling you my story. I guess it wasn't to your liking.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I have a lot on my mind. Fischer looks around the bar. There are several STERN-LOOKING CHARACTERS paying him too much attention. INT. HOTEL LOBBY - CONTINUOUS Arthur and Ariadne sit at a table across the lobby. They spot Cobb moving across the lobby towards Fischer.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And there goes Mr. Charles.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Who or what, exactly, is Mr. Charles?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: It's a gambit designed to turn Fischer against his own subconscious. INT. HOTEL LOBBY BAR - CONTINUOUS Cobb approaches the bar, watched closely by Fischer's Sub- security.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Mr. Fishcer! Good to see you again. Rod Green, Marketing. (to Blonde) And you must be...
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Leaving. She presses against Fischer as she slides off her stool and deposits a cocktail napkin in front of him.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: In case you get bored. Cobb watches her walk away. The Sub-security FOLLOWS her.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I think you just got blown off... unless her phone number really does have only six digits. Fischer glances at the napkin: "528-491." INT. HOTEL LOBBY - CONTINUOUS Arthur watches the Sub-security follow the Blonde.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: And why don't you approve?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Because it involves telling the mark that he's dreaming. Which involves attracting a lot of attention to us.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Didn't Cobb say never to do that?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You must've noticed by now how much time Cobb spends doing things he says never to do.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: . INT. HOTEL LOBBY BAR - CONTINUOUS Cobb turns to Fischer.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Strange way to make friends. (off look) Lifting your wallet, I mean. Fischer pats his pocket. Empty. He looks to the lobby where he sees the Sub-security trailing the Blonde.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Goddamn it. The wallet alone's worth-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Five hundred bucks. I know. Don't worry, my guys are on it.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Who did you say you were? Fischer looks at him, curious. Cobb plows on, confident-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I said I was Rod Green from Marketing-but I'm not. My name is Mr. Charles. I might seem familiar to you. I'm in charge of your security here. INT. HOTEL LOBBY - CONTINUOUS The Blonde hurries up to Saito, emerging from the elevator-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Mr. Saito, can I have a minute? She pushes him back into the elevator, closing the door as the Sub-security approaches... INT. ELEVATOR - CONTINUOUS The Blonde fondles Saito's lapels, getting close.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: I'm sorry, but... Saito glances over her shoulder to see, in the tunnel of infinite reflections created by the elevator's opposing mirrors, three reflections in, THE BLONDE IS EAMES. He winks.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: (pushing him away) Very amusing, Mr. Eames.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You look a bit perkier. A SHUDDER ripples through the elevator.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Turbulence on the plane.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Feels closer. That's Yusuf's driving. And we-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Security? You work for the hotel?
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: No. My specialty is subconscious security.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: You're talking about dreams. You're talking about extraction.
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: Exactly. My job is to protect you... Behind Fischer a WAITER puts down a tray- tipping a champagne glass over- SMASH- Cobb NOTICES. Pauses, looks across the bar- HIS TWO CHILDREN ARE CROUCHED, BACKS TOWARDS US... Cobb looks around the bar, the patrons start to STARE at Cobb, suspicious- Cobb shifts back to Fischer-
direction.name: direction

direction.raw_text: My job is to protect you from any attempt to access your mind through your dreams. Cobb regains his patter- the patrons lose interest... INT.
